A. Hospital revenue & billing operations
Pivot A1 ‚Äî Total revenue trends by Hospital / Insurance / Doctor

Source: Data Model / Table

Rows: Hospital (or Insurance Provider / Doctor ‚Äî create separate pivots for each)

Columns: Year or Month (group Admission Date by Months/Years)

Values: Sum of Billing Amount (primary), Count of Patient ID (secondary if you have Patient ID; otherwise Name)

Filters / Slicers: Hospital, Insurance Provider, Doctor, Admission Type, Timeline for Admission Date, Gender, Condition

KPI calculations

Total Billing Amount = SUM(Billing Amount) (in pivot or measure)

Avg Billing per Patient = Total Billing Amount / DISTINCTCOUNT(Patient ID)

In Power Pivot: AvgBillingPerPatient = [TotalBilling] / DISTINCTCOUNT(Table[PatientID])

If no patient ID, use TotalBilling / Count of Name (less ideal if duplicates)

Highest Revenue Contributors = sort pivot by Sum of Billing Amount descending; show top N.

Notes:

Use a Pivot Chart (line or stacked column) for trend over time; use slicers + timeline for interactivity.

Use conditional formatting to highlight hospitals/insurance/doctor rows where revenue is in top 10%.

Pivot A2 ‚Äî Which conditions generate highest billing?

Rows: Medical Condition

Columns: none (or Hospital to compare across hospitals)

Values: Sum of Billing Amount, Count of Patients

Filters / Slicers: Month/Year, Insurance Provider, Doctor

KPI / Analysis

Avg Billing per Condition = Sum(Billing Amount) / Count(Patients)

Sort by Sum of Billing Amount to see total revenue by condition.

Create a Pareto/Top-10 bar chart to show the conditions responsible for ~80% revenue.

Pivot A3 ‚Äî Identify underperforming hospitals and doctors

Rows: Hospital (or Doctor)

Values: Sum of Billing Amount, Count of Patients, Average LOS (see below)

Calculated fields/measures:

RevenuePerPatient = Sum(Billing Amount)/Count(PatientID)

AvgLOS = AVERAGE(Length of Stay)

Filters: Year/Month, exclude outliers if needed

How to flag underperformers (practical rule):

Compute RevenuePerPatient for all hospitals/doctors.

Calculate percentile thresholds (use PERCENTILE.INC on the RevenuePerPatient range).

Underperformer = those below the 25th percentile AND with negative/flat revenue trend over last 3 months.

Also flag those with AvgLOS significantly higher than cohort average (possible inefficiency).

Conditional formatting rules

RevenuePerPatient < 25th percentile ‚Üí red

Revenue growth month-over-month < 0 ‚Üí warning icon

